00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:08.500
The Canadian Broadcasting Corporation (CBC)

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:12.500
Canada’s national public broadcaster has been providing Canadians with radio and television programming for 75 years.

00:00:13.500 --> 00:00:16.500
It is one of Canada’s largest cultural institutions.

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:19.500
The Broadcasting Act sets out objectives for the CBC.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:25.500
Offers radio and television services that offer a wide range of programming that informs, enlightens and entertains.

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:29.500
The CBC should: be predominantly and distinctively Canadian 

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:32.500
reflect all of Canada and its regions

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:36.500
actively contribute to the flow and exchange of cultural expression

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:40.500
be in English and in French, reflecting the different needs and circumstances of official language communities

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:44.500
reflect the multicultural and multiracial nature of Canada

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:49.500
The CBC offers services in both English and French across Canada.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:55.500
The French-language services include: 31 Première Chaîne and Espace Musique stations

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:59.500
13 Radio-Canada TV stations

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:03.500
Specialty TV channels - ARTV and RDI

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.500
Online services - Bande à part and tou.tv

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:12.500
English-language services include: 51 Radio One and Radio Two stations

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:16.500
16 CBC Television stations

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:19.500
Specialty TV channels bold, documentary, and CBC News Network

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:23.500
Online services Radio 3 and cbc.ca

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:25.500
The CBC is non-profit.

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:34.500
Its revenues comes from several sources: Parliament: 60% - Advertising from conventional TV: 18% - Specialty TV (subscriptions and advertising): 9% - Other sources: 13%

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:43.500
Breakdown of expenditures – by service: Conventional television: 62% - Radio: 19.3% - Specialty TV: 6.7% - Other: 12%

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:51.500
Canadian vs Non-Canadian programming - CBC Television - 90.8% Canadian - 9.2%  Non-Canadian

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:57.500
Télévision de Radio-Canada - 97.5% Canadian - 2.5% Non-Canadian

